1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:14,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:35,620 --> 00:01:38,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:42,000
[Episode 2]

4
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:48,150
Who is that?

5
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:49,940
[Hi.]

6
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:51,310
[Are you Mr Zhou Chuan?]

7
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:54,300
[I'm Chu Li, the editor of
Yuan Yue Books.]

8
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:55,759
[Here's the thing.]

9
00:01:55,780 --> 00:01:57,430
[I sent you a message yesterday.]

10
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:58,950
[But you didn't reply to it.]

11
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:01,280
[That's why I came to find you.]

12
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:03,620
[Why her?]

13
00:02:03,789 --> 00:02:05,270
Our deputy editor wants me

14
00:02:05,270 --> 00:02:08,090
to talk to you about
the new book contract.

15
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,390
Zhou Chuan doesn't live here.

16
00:02:10,390 --> 00:02:11,500
You got the wrong person.

17
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,750
I got the wrong person?

18
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:25,050
It's 2070 though.

19
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:28,790
Could there be two houses
numbered 2070 here?

20
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:33,480
[Zhou Chuan]

21
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,470
Zhou Chuan.

22
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:49,510
Who is that?

23
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:51,030
[Are you Mr Zhou Chuan?]

24
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,910
Here's an important parcel
that needs your signature.

25
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:55,220
What parcel?

26
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:58,750
Are you really Mr Zhou Chuan?

27
00:03:01,230 --> 00:03:02,760
You deceived me!

28
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:03,750
No.

29
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,350
I'm truly sorry, Mr Zhou Chuan.

30
00:03:05,350 --> 00:03:07,030
For talking to you like this.

31
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,310
I was left with no choice.

32
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:10,260
If I don't see you today, I need to...

33
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,510
Scram!

34
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:19,990
Hello, is this management department?

35
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:22,350
Mr Zhou, I'm really not a con artist.

36
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:23,750
I can explain.

37
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:24,790
Mr Zhou Chuan.

38
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:26,310
Mr Zhou Chuan, open the door, please.

39
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,900
Hurry up, she's over here!

40
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,510
The owner complained that
you're disturbing the residents.

41
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:31,590
Please leave immediately.

42
00:03:31,829 --> 00:03:33,350
I'm not disturbing the residents.

43
00:03:33,350 --> 00:03:34,190
Sirs.

44
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,510
Is there any misunderstanding?

45
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:37,070
I'm here for a business talk.

46
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:38,150
Since you don't want to leave,

47
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,420
we're left with no choice.

48
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,640
Gentlemen, let's have a good talk!

49
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:43,350
Brothers, we can have a good talk!

50
00:03:43,350 --> 00:03:44,520
Let go of me!

51
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,840
Gentlemen, you're so strong.

52
00:03:45,940 --> 00:03:46,860
I know Ms Gu!

53
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,500
Wait a minute!

54
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,470
Ms Gu.

55
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:50,390
Do you still remember me?

56
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,990
We met during your visit to
Yuan Yue Publishing House.

57
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:53,990
Indeed.

58
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:56,040
You even embarrassed me
in front of everyone.

59
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:02,470
I know this girl. Let her go.

60
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,150
It's okay, you may leave now.

61
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,100
Thank you, Ms Gu.

62
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,340
I thought you're smart.

63
00:04:14,410 --> 00:04:18,010
As a girl, you should remain decent.

64
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:23,810
Since Zhou Chuan refuses to show himself,
you won't get to see him.

65
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,149
You should get going.

66
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,920
Had you signed the new book contract
with Xin Dun Books earlier,

67
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,590
you'd have been living in peace, right?

68
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,640
You're full of perseverance indeed.

69
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,820
You came to find me right after
being transferred from Beijing.

70
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:41,840
How much pressure does Xin Dun Books

71
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,920
put on you when it comes to the KPIs?

72
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:46,870
I know.

73
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,180
You refuse to sign
the contract with Xin Dun Books

74
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,170
because you want to
see if there's any company

75
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,150
who can offer you a higher price.

76
00:04:52,150 --> 00:04:54,850
But I'd say Xin Dun Books
offers the best conditions.

77
00:04:55,409 --> 00:04:56,320
Does it?

78
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:59,550
When I signed
the Oriental Beauty with you guys,

79
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:01,110
I really didn't feel that way.

80
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:05,110
This time, we don't plan to set
a minimum number of printed copies.

81
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:06,400
Five million yuan.

82
00:05:06,490 --> 00:05:08,510
To buy the full copyright of the book.

83
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,950
Well, that can save me a lot of trouble.

84
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:13,400
But I'm afraid I will repeat
Jiang Yu Cheng's mistake.

85
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:16,290
If you were to reject me because of this,

86
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,550
that'd be so irrational of you.

87
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,120
I just want to sign the contract

88
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,830
with a more sympathetic editor.

89
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,910
We have plenty of time.

90
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:25,110
After all, I've moved to
this neighbourhood.

91
00:05:25,110 --> 00:05:27,660
You can contact me
once you've made up your mind.

92
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:31,030
Can't you hire a maid to clean your house?

93
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:36,520
Your bag.

94
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,970
Thank you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

95
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,670
Though we live in the same neighbourhood,

96
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:49,350
don't come and bother me.

97
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:51,200
-Goodbye.
-Bye-bye.

98
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,670
You're still here?

99
00:06:00,930 --> 00:06:02,940
Mr Zhou Chuan!

100
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,630
Yuan Yue Publishing House
sincerely wants to work with you.

101
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:06,710
Five minutes.

102
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:07,760
No, two minutes!

103
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,990
Just give me two minutes.

104
00:06:09,990 --> 00:06:11,790
Mr Zhou Chuan, why don't you

105
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:13,190
have a listen to the contract conditions

106
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,740
before rejecting me?

107
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,270
Mr Zhou Chuan.

108
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:18,710
Mr Zhou Chuan, are you listening?

109
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:20,190
Turn to the first page of the contract.

110
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,090
Read out the amount.

111
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:26,680
Forty thousand yuan.

112
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:40,390
You can decide on the restaurant.

113
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:41,560
I've been away for three years.

114
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,540
I seriously have no idea what's good here.

115
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:47,320
All right, bye.

116
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,159
Long time no see.

117
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,490
Why are you here?

118
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:23,950
Here's the book you asked for.

119
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,360
-Take it.
-Sure.

120
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,490
I'm taking off.

121
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:29,470
Well,

122
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:31,390
can't you hire a maid to clean the house?

123
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:35,080
Monstress said the same thing just now.

124
00:07:37,710 --> 00:07:38,909
I'm aware that she was here.

125
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,500
You bumped into each other?

126
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:41,860
What a pity.

127
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:44,290
I didn't get to see
the mighty waves beating the shore.

128
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:46,020
The mighty waves beating the shore?

129
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,640
The waves would wash
your dead body ashore.

130
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:49,590
I'll get going.

131
00:07:52,470 --> 00:07:55,720
[Yuan Yue Publishing House]

132
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:01,300
Chief Editor Yu.

133
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,400
I went to meet Mr Zhou Chuan.

134
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,430
But he's very dissatisfied
with our contract.

135
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:08,290
Could we increase
the minimum number of printed copies?

136
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:11,130
Do you know what is
a minimum number of printed copies?

137
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:15,230
A minimum number of
printed copies is a figure

138
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:16,670
given by the circulation department

139
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:19,160
after a market analysis based on
the author's previous sales.

140
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,540
No one can simply change it.

141
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,910
Well, I've got something on.
I'm taking off.

142
00:08:25,990 --> 00:08:28,840
You may see Mr Liang Chong Lang
from the circulation department.

143
00:08:28,990 --> 00:08:29,840
Sure.

144
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,560
Thank you, Chief Editor Yu.

145
00:08:33,710 --> 00:08:34,800
The minimum amount is
three thousand copies.

146
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,020
Not more than that.

147
00:08:36,110 --> 00:08:37,610
But the editors in charge...

148
00:08:37,610 --> 00:08:38,929
What do the editors know?

149
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:39,990
Do they know the market?

150
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:41,380
Do they know marketing?

151
00:08:41,549 --> 00:08:42,630
If they do,

152
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:44,190
what did they hire me for?

153
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,320
Listen.

154
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,320
This is the era of big data.

155
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,280
We can calculate

156
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,750
how many copies can an author sell.

157
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:52,170
He's a new author.

158
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:53,870
And you want to get him
eight thousand copies.

159
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:55,510
Who gave you the confidence?

160
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:56,640
What do we do if we don't sell them out?

161
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,270
Paste them on the wall?

162
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,470
Three thousand it is.

163
00:08:59,470 --> 00:09:00,790
We can't do more than that.

164
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:01,630
Hey.

165
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,550
Mr Liang has made
himself clear, hasn't he?

166
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:05,590
-Hurry, go ahead.
-I'm going ahead.

167
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:07,750
You get back here.

168
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,680
Keep an eye on him.

169
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,760
Don't let him stir up trouble.

170
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,880
Just leave it to me.

171
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,950
Come in.

172
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,420
Hello, Mr Liang.

173
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,960
I'm Chu Li from the second section.

174
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,200
And I'd like to ask you to increase

175
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,520
the minimum number of printed copies of
Mr Zhou Chuan's new book.

176
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:30,360
Here's some data reports
about him that I came up with.

177
00:09:36,430 --> 00:09:37,310
[Zhou Chuan Data Reports]

178
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,920
If I remember correctly,

179
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,680
I've decided on his minimum number
of printed copies long ago.

180
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:43,790
Right?

181
00:09:44,590 --> 00:09:47,000
If that's the case,
why are you here to find me?

182
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,240
Are you doubtful about my decision?

183
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,120
Or do you think you did

184
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,700
better homework than me?

185
00:09:52,950 --> 00:09:54,030
Listen.

186
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:56,440
Zhou Chuan's minimum number of
printed copies cannot be changed.

187
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,360
If you can't get him sign the contract,
that's useless of you.

188
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:01,480
There are some in the editorial department
who have had contracts with great authors

189
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,070
with a lowest number of printed copies.

190
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:04,610
For example, Miao.

191
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,130
Can you learn from them?

192
00:10:06,270 --> 00:10:07,320
Get out!

193
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:19,730
[The Shadow Killer]

194
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:21,230
[The Disappearing Zoo]

195
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,290
[The Disappearing Zoo]

196
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,000
Mr Luo.

197
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,160
Ms Gu.

198
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,220
Are you busy?

199
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,520
Not at all.

200
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:45,050
Let me tell you something.

201
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,560
Mr Li Yu would like to purchase
the right to Jiang Yu Cheng's

202
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:48,510
The Disappearing Zoo.

203
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:50,650
He gave a call to the big boss.

204
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,960
Li Yu?

205
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,030
That's right.

206
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,640
You've been nurturing
Jiang Yu Cheng after all.

207
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:59,110
It shouldn't be a problem
to leave it to you, right?

208
00:11:04,610 --> 00:11:05,630
Xiao Niao.

209
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:08,050
How's your negotiation with
Jiang Yu Cheng going?

210
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,920
I've asked my uncle to contact him.

211
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:12,200
We should hear from him very soon.

212
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:13,800
Great.

213
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:17,450
Jiang Yu Cheng is much
easy than Zhou Chuan.

214
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:19,630
I'm doing this

215
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,880
because I hope you can seal the contract

216
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,480
before Chu Li does.

217
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:26,730
Therefore, you need to work hard.

218
00:11:27,350 --> 00:11:28,230
Got it.

219
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,240
Thank you, Chief Editor Miao.

220
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,410
It's Deputy Editor.

221
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,730
Get back to your work.

222
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:37,150
Deputy Editor Miao.

223
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:39,100
I bought you this coffee.

224
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,080
I don't know if it's
your favourite flavour.

225
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,810
If you don't like it,
I can go get another one.

226
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,010
Sure, thank you.

227
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,520
I heard that you met Zhou Chuan.

228
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,830
How's the negotiation going?

229
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:54,890
I didn't even have the chance to

230
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:58,070
to hand the contract to him
and have it thrown at my face.

231
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:00,710
Is it because you're
not good at negotiating?

232
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,800
Mr Liang told me

233
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:05,400
to ask you about negotiation techniques.

234
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,920
Deputy Editor Miao,
how did you manage the negotiation?

235
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,040
How did you decide on the figure?

236
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,120
All right.

237
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,720
Let me ask you something, Chu Li.

238
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:15,460
How many

239
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,030
minimum copies do you
think we should give him?

240
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,820
One hundred thousand.

241
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,680
The first royalty for an author

242
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:25,030
is determined by the minimum
number of printed copies.

243
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,600
If he manages to receive a royalty of 15%,

244
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,650
that's impressive enough.

245
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:31,480
The figure he receives

246
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,590
is determined by the cost that I can bear.

247
00:12:33,590 --> 00:12:35,630
We're running a publishing house here.

248
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,090
Our boss is a businessman.

249
00:12:37,110 --> 00:12:39,080
And he needs to make money.

250
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,080
Zhou Chuan.

251
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,600
He's got only one best-selling book.

252
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,560
Whether his next book is good or bad,

253
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,490
how his writing is,

254
00:12:45,490 --> 00:12:46,840
none of us has a clue.

255
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,680
In our industry,

256
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,110
successful debut authors

257
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,660
can be found everywhere.

258
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:54,760
And when it comes to ordinary authors,

259
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,280
our publishing house offers

260
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:58,390
three to five thousand yuan.

261
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,720
But we paid Zhou Chuan

262
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,800
thirty thousand yuan
for his first payment.

263
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,480
And we increased it
to forty thousand yuan.

264
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,970
It's enough to prove

265
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,290
that our publishing house

266
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:08,060
has a very high regard for him.

267
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,230
But

268
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:13,240
if I were to tell Mr Zhou Chuan this,

269
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,840
I'm afraid he'd beat me up

270
00:13:14,930 --> 00:13:17,640
and send my body back here
through cash on delivery.

271
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:21,710
And we wouldn't pay for that.

272
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,010
Are you really an idiot?

273
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:28,320
This conversation is between you and me.

274
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,800
How you're going to deliver
the message to Zhou Chuan,

275
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,080
that has to do with
your communication skills.

276
00:13:39,350 --> 00:13:42,340
[Zhou Chuan, Author: Something happened
and I'm not happy about it.]

277
00:13:42,340 --> 00:13:44,920
[When I'm angry, I can't help but wonder]

278
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,640
Is the Zhou Chuan on Weibo

279
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:49,210
[if I'm being mistreated
because I don't work hard enough.]

280
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,210
the same as the one I met
during the daytime?

281
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:51,560
[Perhaps I still need to
keep working hard]

282
00:13:49,380 --> 00:13:51,410
What gentle positive energy?

283
00:13:51,490 --> 00:13:53,410
He's simply a con man.

284
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:54,130
[so as to earn
the respect that I deserve.]

285
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:22,290
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

286
00:14:16,050 --> 00:14:18,580
[I can't help complaining
about an author.]

287
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,720
[He's being all adorable on Weibo.]

288
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,400
[But he's secretly a hot-tempered man.]

289
00:14:22,780 --> 00:14:25,330
[Zhou Chuan, Author:
The buns taste so bad today.]

290
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:27,050
[Alas, I miss the hometown's meat bun.]

291
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,360
[Mr Zhou Chuan's dog is called Er Gou.]

292
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:32,940
[Zhou Chuan, Author: My Er Gou]

293
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:35,380
Zhou Chuan has to go abroad
for every New Year.

294
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:38,570
But her dad celebrates it
in his hometown.

295
00:14:38,710 --> 00:14:40,180
That means

296
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,720
it's been seven years

297
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:43,890
since Zhou Chuan had
a meat bun from his hometown.

298
00:14:54,590 --> 00:15:02,070
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

299
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:57,560
[People pretend to be nice on Weibo.]

300
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,120
[Someone made me so angry today.]

301
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,660
[Even breathing makes me mad.]

302
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,830
[And I can't do my work well.]

303
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:06,250
Unexpectedly, this fox has a career.

304
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,600
Hello, Dad.

305
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:17,270
I figured out you should be off work.

306
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,040
[How did you know I just arrived home?]

307
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,760
It's been only a few days.

308
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:24,640
Why does it seem that
you've gained weight?

309
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:26,320
Why do you have a double chin?

310
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,840
Seriously? Have I gained weight?

311
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,240
It's probably due to the angle.

312
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,170
How about this? Do I look fat still?

313
00:15:34,010 --> 00:15:35,210
How's it going?

314
00:15:35,380 --> 00:15:36,650
How's your house hunting going?

315
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:37,990
Is the money enough?

316
00:15:38,130 --> 00:15:41,260
It's enough. Don't worry, Dad.

317
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,290
[Are you at your living place?]

318
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:45,450
Make a turn.

319
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:47,370
Let me check out the house.

320
00:15:47,830 --> 00:15:49,080
Sure.

321
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,760
Look, isn't it a nice living space?

322
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,600
[The job is going well.]

323
00:15:57,610 --> 00:15:59,400
And the colleagues treat me very well.

324
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,300
Don't you worry.

325
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,160
Wait, why is it dark?

326
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:07,360
What are you saying?

327
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,410
It's a nice living place

328
00:16:08,410 --> 00:16:09,930
with a broken light.

329
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,570
Well, there's something
wrong with my phone.

330
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:14,520
I'll get it repaired tomorrow.

331
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:16,210
Your Highness.

332
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:18,060
You're finally talking to me.

333
00:16:18,170 --> 00:16:19,790
You're not worth my time.

334
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,120
Take it away.

335
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,320
All right, I'm hanging up.

336
00:16:25,330 --> 00:16:26,280
Rest early.

337
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:27,360
Bye-bye.

338
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,530
Bye-bye. Miss you.

339
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:55,660
[Lass.]

340
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:58,970
[Dad]

341
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,600
[I've transferred you some money.
Get yourself a new phone.]

342
00:16:58,620 --> 00:17:00,620
[You're all alone out there.
Take good care of yourself.]

343
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,330
[Don't be so hard on yourself.]

344
00:17:18,589 --> 00:17:20,349
Auntie Zhang.

345
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:25,280
You can't come to clean for this month?

346
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:28,500
Sure, get well soon.

347
00:17:28,609 --> 00:17:29,690
Got it.

348
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,000
Morning, Er Gou.

349
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:46,000
Stop barking.

350
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:50,390
[Er Gou.]

351
00:17:50,490 --> 00:17:51,760
Stop barking.

352
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:56,420
Your house is not here.

353
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:58,310
Let's go. It's the one behind here.

354
00:18:00,730 --> 00:18:02,120
Er Gou.

355
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,790
It's really you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

356
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:11,670
Mr Zhou Chuan.

357
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,210
I'm sorry for keep bothering you.

358
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,600
You're forgiven. Leave now.

359
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:19,710
Come, Er Gou.

360
00:18:19,710 --> 00:18:21,510
Don't ever eat food given by strangers.

361
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:22,490
Mr Zhou Chuan.

362
00:18:22,490 --> 00:18:24,370
These are the meat buns I bought

363
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:26,170
from the hometown shop
you recommended online.

364
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,390
Mr Zhou Chuan.

365
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:29,780
Could we have a talk?

366
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:30,990
No need.

367
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:32,370
Er Gou and I have been on a diet.

368
00:18:32,470 --> 00:18:33,040
We're not eating them.

369
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,970
Mr Zhou Chuan.

370
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:37,970
Is your hand all right?

371
00:18:38,210 --> 00:18:39,850
It's okay.

372
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:40,780
Mr Zhou Chuan.

373
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,720
Could I have a minute of your time

374
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,920
to talk about your new novel
and the figure on the contract?

375
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,640
They're all negotiable.

376
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,610
Thank you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

377
00:19:08,610 --> 00:19:09,650
Have a seat.

378
00:19:41,550 --> 00:19:43,750
You're Mr Zhou Chuan?

379
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:47,250
And now you're calling me that.

380
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,230
Mr Zhou Chuan.

381
00:19:50,310 --> 00:19:52,410
That was ignorant of me.

382
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:54,520
Mr Zhou Chuan, please pardon me.

383
00:19:54,620 --> 00:19:55,980
Cut it out.

384
00:19:56,470 --> 00:19:58,180
You have only two minutes.

385
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:01,130
I...

386
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,360
Sir.

387
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,390
It's bad for health to drink coffee
in the morning on an empty stomach.

388
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:06,380
Have some bun first.

389
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:08,610
Thanks.

390
00:20:08,610 --> 00:20:09,690
But I'd like to remind you

391
00:20:09,690 --> 00:20:12,980
that these buns don't worth as much as
the royalty of hundreds of thousands yuan.

392
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:16,490
Though the minimum number of
printed copies is forty thousand,

393
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:17,610
it's the highest figure
Yuan Yue Publishing House

394
00:20:17,610 --> 00:20:19,890
has had from the past two years.

395
00:20:19,890 --> 00:20:21,720
Our company is very sincere

396
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,910
to you. The sun and the moon
are the witnesses.

397
00:20:24,010 --> 00:20:25,330
Then you go ask the sun and the moon

398
00:20:25,410 --> 00:20:27,650
if I deserve to be
humiliated by these figures.

399
00:20:27,790 --> 00:20:29,650
The sun and the moon are the witnesses?

400
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:31,400
What have I done to deserve this?

401
00:20:31,490 --> 00:20:32,410
Mr Zhou Chuan.

402
00:20:32,410 --> 00:20:33,540
We're not humiliating you.

403
00:20:33,650 --> 00:20:34,570
I guarantee.

404
00:20:34,570 --> 00:20:35,890
If you sign the contract with us,

405
00:20:35,890 --> 00:20:38,330
I will definitely take care of
the publication of your book.

406
00:20:38,330 --> 00:20:39,580
We can even make it two hundred thousand,

407
00:20:39,670 --> 00:20:41,530
not to mention one hundred thousand.

408
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:43,350
That's an empty promise.

409
00:20:43,630 --> 00:20:45,120
You could say whatever you want.

410
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:48,770
Time's up.

411
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:49,570
Thank you for your buns.

412
00:20:49,570 --> 00:20:51,400
Though mine isn't some cheap coffee.

413
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,230
Mr Zhou Chuan.

414
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:54,590
If I remember correctly,

415
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:56,450
your Oriental Beauty

416
00:20:56,450 --> 00:20:58,330
has had three printings.

417
00:20:58,330 --> 00:20:59,360
Are you not confident

418
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:01,090
with Book of Luo He?

419
00:21:01,940 --> 00:21:03,210
Are you trying to provoke me?

420
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:07,000
Of course I'm confident with my work.

421
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:08,670
Me too.

422
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:11,230
It's just that Yuan Yue Publishing House
doesn't deserve it.

423
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:12,970
In fact, you care not only

424
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,350
the minimum number of printed copies.

425
00:21:14,430 --> 00:21:16,990
Otherwise, you'd have signed
the contract with Xin Dun Books.

426
00:21:18,490 --> 00:21:19,810
Cut it out.

427
00:21:19,890 --> 00:21:21,180
Please leave.

428
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:31,190
[Time Is Like A Song]

429
00:21:32,930 --> 00:21:34,330
Yuan Yue Books is where Mr Zhou Gu Xuan

430
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:35,930
created his sales miracle.

431
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:38,730
Don't you want to surpass
your father in his battlefield

432
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:40,290
and become the new miracle?

433
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:46,890
I admit

434
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:49,630
that Yuan Yue Publishing House's
conditions are of average.

435
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:51,760
On the surface, you seem to be unwilling.

436
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:54,050
But you've listened to
the contract contents for times.

437
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:55,330
Actually, you're kind of

438
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:57,980
interested in working with
Yuan Yue Books, right?

439
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,710
You're a newbie, aren't you?

440
00:22:00,540 --> 00:22:02,300
You're so full of yourself.

441
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:06,070
Yes, I'm a newbie.

442
00:22:06,150 --> 00:22:07,890
Naturally, I'm no match for

443
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:09,330
those amazing editors.

444
00:22:09,330 --> 00:22:12,530
And you might find
what I'm saying all empty talk.

445
00:22:12,530 --> 00:22:13,440
But what I know is that,

446
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,750
if I don't manage to sign the contract
and publish your book,

447
00:22:15,850 --> 00:22:18,570
there's no way I can stay at
the Yuan Yue Publishing House.

448
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,330
So, compared to those amazing editors,

449
00:22:20,430 --> 00:22:23,080
I am more determined.

450
00:22:23,210 --> 00:22:24,950
Please, Mr Zhou Chuan.

451
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:26,170
Please.

452
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:29,130
Let's sign the contract.

453
00:22:31,430 --> 00:22:32,590
Are you done talking?

454
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:35,300
Leave.

455
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:49,650
Mr Zhou Chuan.

456
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:51,300
This is my name card.

457
00:22:51,410 --> 00:22:53,040
If you ever change your mind,

458
00:22:53,050 --> 00:22:54,820
contact me anytime.

459
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:02,000
[Chu Li, Literary Editor,
Phone, WeChat, Email, QQ]

460
00:23:01,220 --> 00:23:02,460
I'll put it here.

461
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,750
I'm leaving.

462
00:23:24,010 --> 00:23:24,850
Let me give you a hand.

463
00:23:24,850 --> 00:23:26,450
Sure. Thank you.

464
00:23:26,450 --> 00:23:27,170
Okay.

465
00:23:27,270 --> 00:23:29,080
-Let me do it from here.
-Sure.

466
00:23:29,410 --> 00:23:30,710
Here.

467
00:23:37,090 --> 00:23:39,090
-Well, thank you.
-You're welcome.

468
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,080
Is this your bookstore?

469
00:23:49,490 --> 00:23:50,760
Please come in if you want to buy books.

470
00:23:50,850 --> 00:23:52,330
Can't I have a tour?

471
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:56,620
Well, help yourself.

472
00:23:57,010 --> 00:23:59,450
Someone wants to buy the right
to The Disappearing Zoo.

473
00:24:10,910 --> 00:24:12,940
Your bookstore is doing not bad.

474
00:24:14,130 --> 00:24:16,280
Thank you. Please take a seat.

475
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:30,020
Let's get down to business.

476
00:24:31,420 --> 00:24:33,130
The agreement says that

477
00:24:33,350 --> 00:24:36,520
Xin Dun Books owns the right to
The Disappearing Series for ten years.

478
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:40,010
And now Mr Li Yu has eyes for
The Disappearing Zoo,

479
00:24:40,010 --> 00:24:41,330
and wants to make it into a movie.

480
00:24:43,250 --> 00:24:45,140
It's a very good opportunity.

481
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:47,650
What about you?

482
00:24:48,140 --> 00:24:51,050
What's your role in it?

483
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,610
If you agree to sell the right,

484
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:55,650
I will have a meeting with the director,

485
00:24:55,650 --> 00:24:59,580
the producers, and you.

486
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,220
The original author must join it.

487
00:25:02,220 --> 00:25:03,860
That's the only request from the director.

488
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:07,900
Then no need.

489
00:25:08,130 --> 00:25:09,380
I'm not selling the right.

490
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,470
Do you have to avoid me?

491
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:15,610
We're talking about Li Yu.

492
00:25:16,010 --> 00:25:18,300
There are many authors
who want to work with him.

493
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:22,460
I'm not avoiding you.

494
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:25,370
I just want to have
nothing to do with you.

495
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:32,280
You don't always come across
this kind of opportunity, Jiang Yu Cheng.

496
00:25:33,850 --> 00:25:36,930
Do you want to hide here
running the bookstore forever?

497
00:25:46,770 --> 00:25:50,550
Did I get Mr Zhou Chuan wrong?

498
00:25:51,670 --> 00:25:54,970
How should I persuade him tomorrow?

499
00:25:58,580 --> 00:26:00,690
Xiao Bai, where's your boss?

500
00:26:00,690 --> 00:26:02,070
He left early today.

501
00:26:02,140 --> 00:26:04,040
I too have no idea where he went.

502
00:26:05,220 --> 00:26:06,370
Fine.

503
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:18,850
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

504
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:14,850
[It's another ugly rejection.]

505
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:15,910
[I'd say that]

506
00:26:15,940 --> 00:26:18,900
[the dog of that author
is friendlier than him.]

507
00:26:18,850 --> 00:26:32,440
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

508
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:22,290
[I showed him my utmost sincerity]

509
00:26:22,290 --> 00:26:24,810
[and asked him to
sign a publishing contract.]

510
00:26:24,810 --> 00:26:27,730
[And it's the first time
I bought a man breakfast.]

511
00:26:27,730 --> 00:26:30,170
[He said it's not worth the royalty
of hundreds of thousands yuan.]

512
00:26:30,170 --> 00:26:31,740
[It's not about a bun.]

513
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,440
[It's about my girly heart.]

514
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:38,430
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

515
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:36,080
Why does this experience

516
00:26:36,250 --> 00:26:38,510
seem so familiar?

517
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:54,360
[Chu Li, Literary Editor,
Phone, WeChat, Email, QQ]

518
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:55,720
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

519
00:26:59,860 --> 00:27:01,040
[Chu Li, Literary Editor
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

520
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:05,530
[The Monkey is Chu Li?]

521
00:27:10,010 --> 00:27:11,760
Good morning.

522
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:13,770
Welcome. It's you.

523
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:18,220
Where's your copy of Time Is Like A Song?

524
00:27:18,310 --> 00:27:21,210
I remember it's placed
alongside Oriental Beauty.

525
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:24,150
I want to compare them for something.

526
00:27:24,270 --> 00:27:25,620
We're going to change the display stand.

527
00:27:25,620 --> 00:27:27,850
You can go check them out
from the bookshelf behind there.

528
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:31,600
Sure.

529
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:42,240
[Wait, why am I avoiding her?]

530
00:27:42,970 --> 00:27:49,350
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

531
00:27:42,990 --> 00:27:46,070
[Do you think I should
pay him a third visit?]

532
00:27:46,180 --> 00:27:49,840
[I'll buy him a more classy-looking congee
with pork and century egg tomorrow.]

533
00:28:13,330 --> 00:28:15,490
Mr Zhou Chuan.

534
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:23,460
What a coincidence.

535
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,320
I'll get going.

536
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,250
Wait a minute.

537
00:28:27,470 --> 00:28:29,900
Mr Zhou Chuan,
I'm not trying to be a nagger.

538
00:28:29,990 --> 00:28:31,420
What I told you this morning,

539
00:28:31,430 --> 00:28:33,710
could you give it another thought?

540
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:37,770
I'll give it some thought.

541
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:00,550
Jiang Yu Cheng.

542
00:29:00,650 --> 00:29:01,840
Jiang...

